Rating: 3
This dish is fantastic! I make this dish regularly to rave reviews. I marinate the chicken for the full 2 hours and then sear the chicken. It makes the meat extra moist and flavorfull. I serve it with wild rice and grilled vegetables. I have never had a complaint and a monkey could make this recipe, great for first time cooks and newlyweds.

Rating: 2
I prepared this in a similar way to A Cook from Leucadia, CA - I marinated the chicken (as indicated by the recipe - 2 hours tops), then cooked it in olive oil (I don't have a grill) & added a sauce made with chopped onion, garlic, tomatillos, tomatoes, cilantro & 1 chile in adobo. Perfect, fresh & easy. ITA that this is a good basic marinade for adding extra flavor to cooked chicken. I'll try melting some cheese over the top when I reheat it. mmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm

Rating: 2
I marinated the chicken for 24 hours and found the tequila to be overwhelming. I would recommend marinating it for less time, or perhaps, reducing the ratio of tequila to lime juice. It was interesting, but I prefer a marinade of pure lime juice.

