Rating: 4
This was soooo good. I added a little olive oil, crushed garlic and cilantro to the marinade. The key is to keep basting the chicken. I used a grill pan, it worked great. I sliced the chicken and laid it on top of a sauce made from 1/2 avacado, 1 tomatillo, cilantro to taste and a dash of olive oil! FANTASTIC! I served with mexican corn recipe from epicurious. The whole meal is a YUM! Alot of eye appeal too!

