I add a tablespoon of olive oil to the marinade. This chicken is great for fajitas or on it's own. My family loves it.

Rating: 1
You need to have more fun with this recipe. I made up my own margarita chicken fajita recipe. I marinate the chicken for two days in a marinade made of tequila, triple sec, lime juice, cumin, mashed ripe summer fruit (plums, nectarines, and mangoes are my favorite), tropical fruit coctail, chili powder, and salt. You can roast, stirfry, or grill the marinated chicken. I stirfry accompanying onions, bell peppers, and tomatoes in a sauce made with lime juice, cumin, chili powder, salt, and oil. You can play with the recipe too. Add some fresh orange juice. Or throw in some fresh jalapenos. Make a spicy pico de Gallo to go with it. BBQ the chicken! Or roast and shred it for chicken tacos. And, of course, serve with real margaritas!

